"Suppose the 1988 season had been scored under the modern Formula 1 points system, where the top ten classified finishers of each race receive 25, 18, 15, 12, 10, 8, 6, 4, 2 and 1 points, but with the championship rule actually in force in 1988 that only each driver's eleven best race results count toward their season total. Under those rules, which driver would have won the 1988 drivers' championship, and with how many points? Return the driver's full name and the total points."
